=3D"color: #000000;">Over the past 100+ years advances in golf technology h=
ave transformed how the game is played, increasing distance, accuracy, and =
consistency. Early golfers used wooden clubs with hickory shafts and Haskel=
l golf balls, which featured a rubber core wrapped in rubber thread. They d=
eveloped a nickname called "Bouncing Billies" because they would travel 30 =
yards farther then previous golf balls. Later, steel shafts improved the ab=
ility and consistency. Graphite shaft, titanium club heads, and multi-layer=
 golf balls have further increased performance. Adjustable drivers allow pl=
ayers to customize their shots, and monitor data like ball speed, spin rate=
, and distance. This helps golfers analyze and improve their swings. Overal=
l, technology has made more golf more precise and accessible for players of=
 all skill levels.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div=
