s wanted to hit the ball farther and more accurately, companies developed l=
ighter and stronger clubs using materials like graphite and titanium. This =
allows for faster swing speeds and better control. Golf ball designs also c=
hange to increase distance and improve speed, helping players have more con=
trol over their shots. In addition, technology such as launch monitors and =
swing analysis tools are created to give players feedback, helping them und=
erstand their own swings and improve more quickly. In the end,&nbsp; golf t=
echnology changed&nbsp; to maximize player performance, increase distance a=
nd forgiveness and to keep the game competitive.</span></p></div></div></di=
